Package nusri.fyp.demo.service

Class ReviewService

java.lang.Object
nusri.fyp.demo.service.ReviewService
@Service public class ReviewService extends Object
A service for replay and statistical analysis, providing functionality to process, filter, and gather statistics on state machine execution logs.
This service handles operations like filtering logs, calculating step durations, and generating statistics based on preset configurations.

  • Method Details

    • filter

      public TreeMap<Long,PresetNode> filter(TreeMap<Long,PresetNode> presetNodes, long duration)
      Filters the given timeline data, retaining the most significant nodes based on their duration and balancing the time intervals.
      This method ensures that only the most significant steps, based on their duration, are kept.
      Parameters:
      presetNodes - The original timeline data, with timestamps as keys and preset nodes as values.
      duration - The total duration of the entire process.
      Returns:
      The filtered timeline, with only the most significant steps.

    • getStepStats

      public List<StepStatsDto> getStepStats(String presetName)
      Retrieves statistics for each step under the specified preset, such as average time and standard deviation.
      This method processes the logs and calculates step-wise statistics based on the timestamps.
      Parameters:
      presetName - The name of the preset.
      Returns:
      A list of StepStatsDto containing the statistics for each step.
